{
  "texts": [
    "Independent analysis of the calibrated data using imaging and geometric modeling methods produce reconstructions that are well characterized by a bright and asymmetric ring-like structure with a diameter of 42 ± 3 µas, a central flux depression with an intensity ratio of >10:1, and a position angle of the brightness asymetry of ∼180 •.",
    "These measurements are consistent with expectations for a SMBH of mass M = (6.5 ± 0.7) × 10 9 M (M 87 * 2017 IV; M 87 * 2017 VI).",
    "A small level of interday variability was also detected, which was analyzed in followup studies (e.g., Georgiev et al. 2022; Satapathy et al. 2022).",
    "Analyses from outside the EHT collaboration featuring both imaging (Carilli & Thyagarajan 2022; Arras et al. 2022) and geometric modeling methods (Lockhart & Gralla 2022) agree that the 2017 EHT data are consistent with a ring-like structure.",
    "There is another external analysis of the 2017 data that claims not to support the EHT interpretation (Miyoshi et al. 2022)."
  ]
}